sense_info_list.en: existing in something as a permanent, essential, or characteristic attribute

examination_example.sentence: Because humans have an <highlight>inherent</highlight> need to resolve uncertainty, according to a recent study in Psychological Science.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 《心理科学》最近的一项研究表明，该问题的原因是人类具有解决不确定性的内在需求。

examination_example.sentence: Good governance rests on an understanding of the <highlight>inherent</highlight> worth of each individual.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 良好的治理有赖于对每个人的内在价值的理解。

examination_example.sentence: The fashion industry knows it has an <highlight>inherent</highlight> problem in focusing on material adornment and idealized body types.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 时尚产业深知，注重衣着装饰和理想化身材是一个根深蒂固的问题。
